The **rent vs buy decision** is one of the most significant financial choices Australians face. With home loan rates at approximately 6.3% and property prices elevated in major cities, the month-to-month cost of buying often exceeds renting. However, over 7–10+ years, ownership builds equity and capital growth that renting cannot replicate.

This calculator compares the true total cost of renting versus buying over your chosen period, including stamp duty, mortgage interest, property maintenance, capital growth, and the opportunity cost of your deposit.
